# Create Organization Account

## Overview

This section documents the configuration for creating the Organization Account. The Organization Account provides centralized management capabilities for your Snowflake environment, including the ability to create and manage other accounts.

## Organization Account Configuration

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| **Account Name** | `{{ org_account_name | upper }}` |
{%- if account_name_prefix | upper != "NONE" %}
| **Full Account Name** | `{{ account_name_prefix }}_{{ org_account_name }}` |
| **Account URL** | `https://{{ snowflake_org_name | upper }}-{{ account_name_prefix }}_{{ org_account_name }}.snowflakecomputing.com` |
{%- else %}
| **Account URL** | `https://{{ snowflake_org_name | upper }}-{{ org_account_name }}.snowflakecomputing.com` |
{%- endif %}
| **Edition** | {{ org_account_edition }} |
| **Cloud Region** | {{ org_account_region }} |

## Initial Administrator

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| **Administrator Username** | {{ org_admin_name }} |
| **Administrator Email** | {{ org_admin_email }} |
| **User Type** | PERSON |
| **Initial Password** | System-generated (must change on first login) |

## Account Details

**Edition: {{ org_account_edition }}**

{%- if org_account_edition == "Enterprise" %}
Enterprise Edition provides full organization management capabilities including:
- Multi-cluster warehouses and concurrency scaling
- Column-level security and up to 90-day Time Travel
- Failover/Failback for business continuity
- Full ORGADMIN functionality for managing child accounts
{%- elif org_account_edition == "Business Critical" %}
Business Critical Edition provides everything in Enterprise, plus:
- HIPAA and PCI DSS compliance support
- Customer-managed encryption keys (Tri-Secret Secure)
- Private connectivity options (PrivateLink)
- Enhanced security for regulated environments
{%- endif %}

**Cloud Region: {{ org_account_region }}**

The Organization Account will be hosted in this region. All administrative operations and organization-level data will reside here.

## Post-Creation Checklist

After the Organization Account is created:

- [ ] Initial administrator logs in and changes password
- [ ] Set up MFA for the initial ACCOUNTADMIN user
- [ ] Add 1-2 additional ACCOUNTADMIN users for redundancy
- [ ] Configure network policies (IP allowlisting) if required
- [ ] Grant ORGADMIN role to appropriate administrators
- [ ] Verify organization-level views are accessible
- [ ] Document account credentials securely

## Important Notes

- The Organization Account should **not** contain business data
- It is used exclusively for administrative and management purposes
- All child accounts will be created from this Organization Account
- ORGADMIN privileges are required to create additional accounts